President Biden has declared a major disaster in Rhode Island due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from September 10 to September 13, 2023. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Affected individuals in Providence County can receive grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other recovery programs. Robert V. Fogel of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations. More designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance at DisasterAssistance.gov or by calling FEMA. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.